Protection of minors online is an area that China has been taking  very seriously for some tim e, and the draft is hopefully a misstep that will be corrected before being finalized.
In determining the appropriate scope of PHM content, regulators need to keep in mind the incidental impact on adults from sidelining this content and the burden on users and platforms in labeling all such content. At the same time, the definition needs to recognize and align with existing legal authority, including that already requiring that “negative content” be kept out of highly-visible areas.
The current framework seems to connect”content harmful to minors” with “illegal content” under the broader content regime, and PHM content with “negative content”, but stops short of fully equating them. If the distinction is to continue with regard to online content, regulators will have to explain what makes PHM more hazardous to minors than other negative content.
